# IoT Smart Weather Station (ESP32 + BME280)

An end-to-end Electronics and Communication Engineering project that monitors environmental data and streams it to a web dashboard.

## 🚀 Overview
This project uses an **ESP32** microcontroller and a **BME280** sensor to measure temperature, humidity, and pressure. Data is transmitted via MQTT to a Node-RED dashboard for real-time visualization.

## 🛠️ Hardware Components
- ESP32 Development Board
- BME280 Sensor (I2C)
- Jumper Wires & Breadboard
- USB-C Cable

## 💻 Tech Stack
- **Language:** C++ (Arduino IDE)
- **Protocol:** MQTT
- **Dashboard:** Node-RED / Adafruit IO
- **Libraries:** Adafruit_BME280, PubSubClient

## 🔌 Circuit Diagram

| ESP32 Pin | BME280 Pin |
|-----------|------------|
| 3.3V      | VCC        |
| GND       | GND        |
| GPIO 21   | SDA        |
| GPIO 22   | SCL        |

## 📈 Key Features
- [x] Real-time sensor data streaming.
- [x] Deep Sleep mode for power efficiency.
- [x] Over-the-Air (OTA) updates.

